1. Disponer de cada folder en el nodo/máquina deseada
    Fuente: https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/copy_module.html

    1. En /etc/ansible/hosts, añadir servidores a emplear
    2. Crear un playbook con:
        - name: Copy file with owner and permissions
          hosts: host afectado
          tasks:
          - name: another one
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /path/to/folder/from/origin
              dest: /path/to/folder/from/dest
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
    Ejemplo:
        - name: copying
          hosts: localhost
          tasks:
          - name: copying frontend
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/app/frontend
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
          - name: copying backend
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/app/backend
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
          - name: copying fetcher
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/app/fetcher
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'
          - name: copying requirements.txt
            ansible.builtin.copy:
              src: /usr/src/requirements.txt
              dest: /usr/src
              owner: root
              group: root
              mode: 'preserve'              

2. Instalar requirements.txt en el nodo/máquina donde se disponga el fetcher:
    Fuente: https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/pip_module.html
            https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26402123/ansible-creating-a-virtualenv
            https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/apt_module.html

    Ejemplo:
    - name: preparing fetcher
      hosts: localhost
      tasks:
      - name: installing pip3
        apt: 
          name: python3-pip
          state: present
    - name: installing python depedencies
      hosts: localhost
      tasks:
      - name: install virtualenv
        pip:
          name: virtualenv
      - name: Install specified python requirements in indicated (virtualenv)
        pip:
          requirements: /usr/src/requirements.txt
          virtualenv: /usr/src/TFM13186
          virtualenv_python:

3. Instalar nodeJs 
  Emplea NVM (Node Version Manager)
  Fuente: https://github.com/morgangraphics/ansible-role-nvm
          https://www.tderflinger.com/en/ansible-node

  3.1. Descargar elementos necesarios en el archivo roles.




  3.2. Utilizar ansible:

    - name: Install curl and wget
      gather_facts: 'no'
      hosts: localhost
      become: yes
      remote_user: root

      tasks:
        - name: Install curl
          yum:
            name: curl
            state: present

        - name: Install wget
          yum:
            name: wget
            state: present

    - name: Create nvm
      hosts: localhost

      roles:
        - role: ansible-role-nvm
          nodejs_version: '10.16.0'
          nvm_commands:
          - "nvm exec default npm install"


